<main id="main" class="policy-page"><section class="page-hero"><div class="shell-narrow"><p class="eyebrow">RESEARCH METHODOLOGY</p><h1>How future decision intelligence will be handled.</h1><p>Enterprise data is not yet commercially available.</p></div></section><section class="shell-narrow policy-content"><h2>Information collected</h2><p>If research activities begin, BOMSociety may collect voluntary, decision-level responses such as a topic selected, an answer to a knowledge check, and optional feedback. Collection will be described before it occurs.</p><h2>Excluded information</h2><p>BOMSociety does not need a physician’s patient information, clinical records, employer credentials, contract documents, or personally identifiable information to provide the public learning path.</p><h2>Anonymity and aggregation</h2><p>Any future reporting will use aggregated results and anonymity safeguards. Individual responses will not be presented as identifiable physician profiles.</p><h2>Minimum sample thresholds</h2><p>No aggregate finding will be published until a minimum sample threshold appropriate to the analysis is documented. Thresholds have not yet been set because there is no commercial enterprise dataset.</p><h2>No sale of personal information</h2><p>BOMSociety will not sell personally identifiable information.</p><h2>Current limitations</h2><p>The current experience uses local browser storage for pathway progress and feedback. It does not establish representative physician benchmarks, rankings, or market conclusions.</p></section></main>
